The National Highways Authority of India has reduced the toll tax collected from road users at Manoharabad (Toopran) tollgate in Medak district. Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao had brought to the notice of NHAI that short distance commuters on the route paid heavily according to the present rates prescribed for car, jeep, van and light motor vehicles. The rates were Rs. 180 and Rs. 125 for up and down and one way respectively. At Mr. Raoâ€™s request for reduction, the rates were revised to Rs. 105 and Rs 70 respectively, a release said.